manpages-cpp is a project that generates C++ man pages from cplusplus.com

cppman, the man page browser/fetcher generates C++ manual pages from cplusplus.com and provide a man-like interface to view man pages.

Arch Linux users can install it from AUR.

Ubuntu PPA can be add with following command:
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:aitjcize/manpages-cpp
